    <item>
      <title>A Lenten Meditation </title>
      <link>http://tobyblog.com/microposts/20190328-a-lenten-meditation/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2019 08:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://tobyblog.com/microposts/20190328-a-lenten-meditation/</guid>
      <description>The soul has to make a choice, and the outcome will either break it into pieces or enable it to sail to its destination in God. And the choice comes down to this: Will the soul accept or reject suffering? Will it make this suffering its own, or struggle against it, seeing it as something alien to itself?
&amp;hellip;If he chooses to accept his suffering, he must embrace it with the wholeness of his life; he must discover and accept the proper relation to his suffering.</description>
    </item>
    
