    <item>
      <title>Forgiveness Sunday</title>
      <link>http://tobyblog.com/microposts/20190310-forgiveness-sunday/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 10 Mar 2019 06:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://tobyblog.com/microposts/20190310-forgiveness-sunday/</guid>
      <description>Today in church I prostrated myself, whuch is to say I bowed deeply, with knees and forehead touching the floor, to my spiritual fathers and to every single other person present, and asked forgiveness for the things I have done that caused them offense. And they in turn asked me. The little kids. The old folks. My personal friends, and people to whom I&amp;rsquo;ve never spoken a word. We forgave each other, and reminded each other that God forgives.</description>
    </item>
    
